{
  "texts": [
    "In supervised learning, massive historical network data contain rich expert settings and module iterations under various network conditions.",
    "It can be used to build large datasets for fine-tuning large FMs in NDT agents and training API calls between different agents.",
    "In RL, NDT agents can interact with the prevalidation environment in DTN to obtain estimated network performance, which can be used for evaluating agent behaviors during the training process in RL.",
    "Specifically, as the pre-validation environment can train NDT agents ahead of time, the concern for timeliness is negligible.",
    "As FMs have hallucinations, even if RL (based agent) converges in the prevalidation environment of NDTs, they must compare the agent's performance with that of traditional expert strategies (via channel state information (CSI)) before they are adopted in the physical world."
  ]
}